	<p pid="a.222.3/1">The Government continue to raise concerns about freedom of expression with the Turkish Government. My right honourable friend the Minister for Europe, Geoff Hoon, underlined the need for further reforms to enhance freedom of expression during his visit to Turkey on <phrase class="date" code="2006-09-11">11 September</phrase>, and my right honourable friend the Prime Minister relayed a similar message when he met his Turkish counterpart on <phrase class="date" code="2006-10-03">3 October</phrase>.</p>
	<p pid="a.222.3/2">We are aware of the prosecution of writer Ipek Calislar under A301 of the Turkish penal code. We will follow her trial closely and raise her case in our representations to the Turkish Government on freedom of expression.</p>
</reply>
